92).\n\nRoulette appeared as part of the \"Hellions\" entry in the ''[[Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Deluxe Edition]]'' #5.\n\n==Fictional character biography==\nJennifer Stavros was born in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]]. As a teenager, Jennifer was recruited into the [[Hellions]]. One of the team's first missions was to stop the [[New Mutants]], who were attacking [[Massachusetts Academy (comics)|the Massachusetts Academy]], the school attended by the Hellions. The Hellions meet with mixed success against the New Mutants, and their headmistress [[Emma Frost]] is forced to step in.<ref>''New Mutants'' #16-17</ref> Roulette begins a guarded flirtation with one of her teammates, [[Empath (comics)|Empath]], with whom she shares an enthusiasm for making others suffer.<ref>''Uncanny X-Men'' #193 (May 1985)</ref> At a dance party attended by both the Hellions and the New Mutants, she turns her charms on New Mutant [[Cypher (comics)|Cypher]] instead. However, after getting drunk Cypher hits her in a paranoid fit.<ref>''New Mutants'' #53</ref>\n\nRoulette was part of the force of Hellions that attacked the New Warriors over the fate of Firestar, a former member. At first, her powers were deflected back on her teammates but when the battles degenerated to one on one, she easily took down [[Robbie Baldwin|Speedball]]. Eventually the Hellions left, having lost due to the competition deal between the White Queen and Tai, the unofficial force behind the Warriors.<ref>''New Warriors'' #9-10 (March\u2013April 1991)</ref>\n\nSoon after, Emma throws another party, which the Hellions as well as the [[X-Men]] Gold team attended. Roulette, along with most of her teammates, is killed by [[Trevor Fitzroy]] in order to fuel his [[time travel]]ing [[Teleportation| teleportation portals]].<ref>off-panel in ''Uncanny X-Men'' #282 (1991)</ref>\n\n===Necrosha===\nRoulette appears in the [[Necrosha]] event in ''New Mutants'' (vol. 3), along with the other deceased Hellions, having been resurrected by [[Selene (comics)|Selene]]'s magic and the [[transmode virus]].<ref>''New Mutants'' volume 3 #7-8 (2010)</ref> She again appears infected with the transmode virus in the \"Fight the Future\" arc of ''New Mutants'' (vol. 3).<ref>''New Mutants'' volume 3 #48-49 (2012)</ref>\n\n==Powers and abilities==\nRoulette's mutant power is to generate disks of psychic energy that alter the laws of chance of anything they touch, resulting in either good or bad luck for their subjects by altering the [[probabilities]] field around the victim at whom she throws the disc. Her black energy discs create \"bad luck\" while her red energy discs bestow \"good luck.\"\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[[MarvelDatabase:Roulette (Jennifer Stavros)]] - profile and picture gallery\n*[http://www.uncannyxmen.net/db/characters/showquestion.asp?fldAuto=896 Uncannyxmen.net character bio on Roulette]\n*[http://www.uncannyxmen.net/db/pov/showquestion.asp?faq=5&fldAuto=24 Uncannyxmen.net feature on the Hellions]\n\n[[Category:Characters created by Chris Claremont]]\n[[Category:Female supervillains]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutants]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]"}]}}}}